# This project mirrors Claude Code's setup use openrouter api and openrouter free model

# Copy to .env and fill in your key.
# --- OpenRouter route (what this project uses) ---
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_MODEL=

# --- Or use Anthropic-style env vars directly (same names Claude Code reads) ---
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=


### Tips（how to use free model in open router in claude cli through script）:

# Option 1 (global setting)：change ~/.claude/settings.json file.

# Add the configuration below in settings.json. You can choose free model you like, here is "openai/gpt-oss-120b:free"

# {
#   "env": {  
#     "ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL":"https://openrouter.ai/api",
#     "ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN”:”your openrouter key”,
#     "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY":"",
#     "ANTHROPIC_MODEL":"openai/gpt-oss-120b:free"
#   },
#   "theme": "auto"
# }

# Option 2 (currrent workspace folder):
# 1. Create .claude folder in this workspace folder
# 2. Create settings.json file under .claude folder 
# 3. Add the configuration above in settings.json.

